The regular work schedules for this project is 9:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m. and 9:00 p.m. to 5:00 a.m. (Monday through Friday). On US 97 Blewett Pass milepost 159-160 (near Swauk Creek Campground) Monday through Friday from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. there is the potential for flagger controlled traffic with delays when the contractor is staging equipment. Traffic has been shifted to a bypass lane with a reduced speed limit and 12 ft. width restriction. The speed reduction and width restrict are in place 24/7. US 97 Boundary Bridge #9323County: Kittitas Highway: US 97 Region: North CentralLocation: MP 159-160 (Swauk Campground)Description: In this $4.5M project WHH Nisqually Construction Services will construct a concrete bridge to replace an old culvert that created a fish passage barrier. Work will include a detour widening to shift traffic while the bridge is constructed half at a time.
